GraphQL is a query language for APIs that lets clients ask for exactly the data they need — nothing more, nothing less.

✅ When You SHOULD Use GraphQL
1️⃣ Multiple Clients, Different Data Needs

**Best case: Web, Mobile, Admin dashboard all hit the same backend.**
Example:

Mobile needs: name + rent

Admin needs: name + rent + owner + payments + history

With REST → multiple endpoints
With GraphQL → one endpoint, different queries
✅ Ideal for:
Web + mobile apps
Public APIs
Admin dashboards



❌ When You Should NOT Use GraphQL
1️⃣ Simple CRUD APIs

If your app is:
Login
Create PG
List rooms
Pay rent
👉 REST is simpler, faster, cheaper

❌ GraphQL adds:
Schema complexity
Resolver overhead
Learning curve